<br>
<br>
Maybe not snare, and maybe not root. But I know for damn sure that his fire based spells would hit full.<br>
<br>
<br>
1) Fire based spells seem harder to resist than any other spells.<br>
<br>
I've been hit by fire based DD spells in PoG even with 190FR.<br>
<br>
Boofy has Ro's sundering.<br>
<br>
Verant changed in the last patch so that debuff spells do 1.5times the amount of debuff resistance in pvp.<br>
<br>
<br>
SOOOO. Ro's sundering now does -60FR in pvp. I'm sure you can get 100FR easy... but even with that, Ro's is nearly unresistable, and will drop your FR to 40FR.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now with 40FR, boofy will be able to hit you with Starfire (600pt DD) and immolate, and any others that he has.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'm not saying that it's for sure that he'll kill you, but I wouldn't rule out the fact that he could kick your ass in a duel.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now as for a bard.<br>
<br>
<br>
You have to get Fire/Magic/cold resistances at least up to 100 before taking me on.<br>
<br>
And even then, i'll still get a couple songs off on you.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'm not trying to get myself into a pissing contest with anyone.<br>
<br>
But melee's are at a real disadvantage when it comes to outdoors.<br>
<br>
<br>
Being a bard, I can out run you.<br>
<br>
Cast until hell freezes over.<br>
<br>
Dispell you.<br>
<br>
Raise my resistances to well over 150<br>
<br>
Charm anything.<br>
<br>
Stun.<br>
<br>
fear.<br>
<br>
Regenerate at higher levels than most melee.<br>
<br>
and many other things.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Jorply. I have no doubt that if I stood toe to toe with you, i'd be dead faster than a n00b taking a swing at the PoD.<br>
<br>
But, you have to realize that a bards life is based on strategy. If we can't beat something solo one way, we run...remem a couple songs, and go back from a different angle.<br>
<br>
Even after verant nerf'd charm kiting so that the monster we charm doesn't remember it's target, I still use charm to solo 2 level 45's at the same time.<br>
<br>
As for the whole pet thing...I can still charm pets. I have done before, and I doubt it'll ever change. The test of tactics...they said you couldn't use charm on other players, but you could use it on pets.<br>
<br>
I'm done with this rant....Maybe when I hit level 60, and get to a point where I think i'm ready to duel some of you guys, i'll actually have some fun, and show you what a bard can do.<br>
